<subSubSection id="96BC651BB73028420D03FA0838A9F993" pageId="21" pageNumber="411" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="DE193690B73028420D03FA0838A9F993" blockId="21.[1367,2573,720,1658]" pageId="21" pageNumber="411">
<emphasis id="ECD2EA82B73028420D03FA08399CFA0E" bold="true" box="[1369,1730,1433,1462]" pageId="21" pageNumber="411">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
CITES Appendix II. Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red Lust (as 
<taxonomicName id="19A64D13B73028420E0AFA2D3981FA65" box="[1616,1759,1468,1501]" class="Mammalia" family="Cebidae" genus="Cebus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="21" pageNumber="412" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albifrons">C. albifrons</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="19A64D13B73028420EB2FA2D381BFA65" authorityName="Hershkovitz" authorityYear="1949" box="[1768,1861,1468,1501]" class="Mammalia" family="Cebidae" genus="Cebus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="21" pageNumber="411" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cesarae">cesarae</taxonomicName>
). The Rio Cesar White-fronted Capuchin occurs in Ciénaga Grande de Santa Marta and Los Flamencos fauna and flora sanctuaries, and probably also in Macuira National Natural Park.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
